WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:05.270
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.291 --> 00:12.679
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWN.org.

00:12.699 --> 00:13.180
Good morning.

00:13.200 --> 00:14.081
My name is Justin.

00:14.141 --> 00:16.644
I'm the pastor of Young Adults and Families.

00:16.864 --> 00:18.907
It's a joy to be with you this morning.

00:19.487 --> 00:20.689
I just want to welcome you.

00:20.909 --> 00:28.338
Thanks for fighting the rain, but I guess if you're just walking in, you're walking in and sunshine and thankful for that.

00:28.450 --> 00:35.400
I want to welcome not only you this morning, but I want to welcome our west campus, our shepherd campus, and as well as 11 East.

00:35.440 --> 00:37.563
Thank you for being here this morning.

00:37.643 --> 00:41.689
If you have a Bible, we're going to be in Deuteronomy chapter 6 this morning.

00:44.212 --> 00:51.282
The past few weeks have left many of us unsettled in light of the recent events with Charlie Kirk, where

00:51.490 --> 01:00.670
Even this afternoon, thousands upon thousands of people are going to gather and celebrate and memorialize his life and celebrate his life.

01:01.452 --> 01:11.474
He's an impactful man, a man who was bold, a man who was courageous, a man who spoke and invested and was a leading voice in the next generation.

01:11.714 --> 01:15.785
And we think about events that occurred just over a week ago.

01:15.805 --> 01:17.490
We think about those events.

01:17.550 --> 01:18.753
Those events shake us.

01:18.854 --> 01:21.782
Those events cause us a stir within us.

01:22.203 --> 01:26.354
They cause us to consider what do we do in the midst of this?

01:26.658 --> 01:37.214
I don't know that any of us can sit by neutral and just watch the events unfold and go, well, how do we just move on about our Tuesday or Wednesday afternoon, right?

01:37.554 --> 01:40.899
Like we see events like that and it feels like an attack.

01:40.979 --> 01:42.982
It feels, it stirs something in us.

01:43.062 --> 01:44.685
We gotta do something.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.608
How do I respond?

01:47.128 --> 01:56.402
And I think in times of grief and times of injustice and times of confusion, when we see such an outrage or we see maybe an opposing culture,

01:56.642 --> 01:59.968
Oftentimes, I think we can fall into two temptations.

02:00.088 --> 02:07.562
The first being that some of us, we just assimilate with culture and we just kind of get caught up in the cultural stream.

02:07.883 --> 02:08.684
And we're going, you know what?

02:08.704 --> 02:09.947
I don't want to really be bold.

02:09.987 --> 02:11.429
I don't really want to be courageous.

02:11.570 --> 02:13.132
I don't want to be a leading voice.

02:13.213 --> 02:15.276
We, we, we concerned about that.

02:15.337 --> 02:20.466
So let me just assimilate into culture and just kind of go underneath the radar, right?

02:20.674 --> 02:25.643
And then there's some of us that just withdraw from culture, and we say, you know what?

02:25.683 --> 02:27.326
I'm going to privatize my faith.

02:27.386 --> 02:28.728
I'm going to go silent about my faith.

02:28.748 --> 02:30.551
I'm going to go underground with my faith.

02:31.112 --> 02:33.877
And I believe the Lord has called us to a third way.

02:34.578 --> 02:41.530
I believe the Lord has called us to influence that we are called to invest, that we're not called to assimilate with culture.

02:41.871 --> 02:45.938
We're not called to withdraw from culture, but we are to engage.

02:46.402 --> 02:52.091
Now, I want to ask you, how did you engage in terms of what happened within the last week?

02:53.013 --> 02:56.779
I think many of us do what we know to do and we go to social media.

02:56.859 --> 02:59.664
We go and we address the concerns.

02:59.744 --> 03:02.709
We speak against these concerns, right?

03:03.029 --> 03:05.934
We wanted to stand against the things that are horrific.

03:05.954 --> 03:08.558
We want to stand with those that are hurting.

03:08.598 --> 03:13.266
And in many ways, going to social media, it feels like courage.

03:14.018 --> 03:16.762
Going to social media, it feels like we're doing something.

03:16.822 --> 03:25.614
It feels like I'm taking a stand and it feels like I want to identify with the good crowd and I care.

03:26.656 --> 03:34.547
But if we're honest this morning, if we're honest, that's the furthest many of us went.

03:36.610 --> 03:39.634
It's the furthest many of us will go.

03:40.866 --> 03:49.115
I mean, Chris Harper, who will be with us next week at our barbecue festival, I think he captured this tension when he said this.

03:50.056 --> 04:01.187
Speaking of social media, speaking about voicing those concerns, he said, many of these things offer the illusion of progress while leaving the real work undone.

04:02.548 --> 04:04.571
Real change requires risk.

04:05.151 --> 04:06.312
It requires cost.

04:06.793 --> 04:07.954
It requires money.

04:08.194 --> 04:09.375
It requires time.

04:09.836 --> 04:11.258
It requires reputation.

04:11.658 --> 04:12.840
It requires comfort.

04:13.621 --> 04:18.306
It's going to require us to do more than just posting our concern.

04:18.687 --> 04:23.172
It's going to do more than us just voicing and showing the world that we care.

04:23.232 --> 04:25.395
It's going to cost us.

04:25.415 --> 04:27.677
We are going to have to invest.

04:27.697 --> 04:29.560
We are going to have to step up.

04:30.941 --> 04:34.866
But what is the real work that Chris Harper calls us to?

04:35.362 --> 04:39.206
What is the real work we're called to do when tragedy strikes?

04:39.526 --> 04:45.572
What is the real work to do when we look around and recognize that the world around us is broken?

04:45.653 --> 04:46.433
It's messed up.

04:46.774 --> 04:49.376
What is ours to carry in this world?

04:50.397 --> 04:55.883
And here's what I would say and I want to encourage you more than any message that I've preached from this stage.

04:55.943 --> 04:57.405
I want to encourage you this morning.

04:57.745 --> 05:02.610
I'm very passionate about this topic because I believe it is very, very strategic.

05:03.426 --> 05:07.950
But the most strategic investment we can make is in the next generation.

05:08.951 --> 05:10.893
Charlie Kirk modeled this.

05:10.913 --> 05:14.276
Charlie Kirk went and he gathered people on college campuses.

05:14.316 --> 05:22.985
He began speaking into life and answering questions and debating and having rhetoric around the questions that we are all wrestling with.

05:23.766 --> 05:25.507
And he answered them consistently.

05:25.527 --> 05:26.989
He answered them with clarity.

05:27.970 --> 05:32.594
And he spoke to some of the issues that our generation is facing.

05:33.890 --> 05:44.327
The greatest and most strategic investment we can make today, the real work that we're called to do is invest in the next generation.

05:44.387 --> 05:56.146
Pastor Ray Orland once said, in his book to the 10th generation, he said this, God gave you a precious family to play a crucial role in his strategy for the redemption of the world.

05:57.186 --> 06:15.475
One of the major strategies, one of the major ways in which God is seeking to bring about change in the world is through the context of a family, that he is going to use your family to influence, that he's going to use your family to invest and bring about change in culture.

06:15.835 --> 06:20.082
So we can't withdraw, we can't assimilate, we must initiate.

06:21.218 --> 06:35.838
Scripture warns us about neglecting this responsibility in Judges chapter 2 verse 10, it says, and there arose another generation after them who did not know the Lord or the work He had done for Israel.

06:36.159 --> 06:37.421
Will that be said about us?

06:39.303 --> 06:46.333
Will that be said about the generation to follow us or our great-grandchildren or great-great-grandchildren?

06:46.393 --> 06:49.778
And I believe, Deuteronomy 6,

06:49.986 --> 06:52.208
gives us the ability to prevent that.

06:52.929 --> 06:59.777
Deuteronomy 6 gives us a clear answer and a call to take responsibility to invest in the next generation.

07:00.157 --> 07:00.918
Hear me this morning.

07:01.138 --> 07:02.920
This is not just a call for parents.

07:03.921 --> 07:08.626
It's a call to all of us to play a crucial role in raising the next generation.

07:09.827 --> 07:19.538
The greatest contribution to still a quote, your greatest contribution to the kingdom of God may not be something you do, but in someone you raise.

07:19.810 --> 07:23.474
but in someone you disciple and someone you invest in.

07:23.494 --> 07:29.000
So let's jump into the text this morning and discover how can we invest where it matters most?

07:29.040 --> 07:32.083
Deuteronomy chapter six, verse four.

07:32.724 --> 07:36.107
It says, hero Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one.

07:36.968 --> 07:41.413
You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your might.

07:41.973 --> 07:46.258
And these words that I command you today shall be on your heart.

07:46.786 --> 07:49.110
You shall teach them diligently to your children.

07:49.170 --> 07:55.400
You should talk of them when you sit in your house and when you walk by the way and when you lie down and when you rise.

07:56.161 --> 08:00.548
You shall bind them as a sign on your hand and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.

08:01.109 --> 08:04.554
You shall write them on the doorpost of your house and on your gates.

08:05.476 --> 08:11.986
And when the Lord God brings you into the land that He swore to your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, to Jacob.

08:12.322 --> 08:33.205
and to give you with great and good cities that you did not build, and houses full of good things that you did not fill, and cisterns that you did not dig, and vineyards and olive trees that you did not plant, and when you eat and are full, then take care lest you forget the Lord who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.

08:33.605 --> 08:41.874
Now, in this text in Deuteronomy 6, what we have is what is known in Jewish culture as the Shema.

08:42.242 --> 08:45.527
The Shema is this passage of Scripture that we read.

08:45.567 --> 08:46.308
It's a prayer.

08:46.669 --> 08:50.735
It's a prayer that faithful Jews would recite twice a day.

08:50.755 --> 08:54.280
That they would do that when they rose and when they went to bed.

08:54.841 --> 08:57.946
They would recite this frequently.

08:58.006 --> 09:04.536
And I want you to imagine practicing this repetition in your home, in your life, with regularity.

09:05.157 --> 09:11.026
Now, I totally understand that with many things that have regular repetition that sometimes

09:11.138 --> 09:14.302
It can become more form without the substance.

09:14.403 --> 09:17.427
It can become more form and lose the passion.

09:17.487 --> 09:34.290
But I want you to imagine for just a moment that you begin your day and end your day with this passage of Scripture to love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, all your mind and to teach these things to your children diligently and not to forget the Lord.

09:34.722 --> 09:42.612
I think that practice alone would radically change how we wake up and how we rise and how we go about living our day.

09:43.593 --> 09:47.378
And so what I want us to do this morning is I want us to look in this passage.

09:47.398 --> 09:50.261
I want us to identify what is the real work that we need to carry.

09:50.341 --> 09:53.045
How can we invest in the next generation?

09:53.125 --> 10:00.754
It may not start like you think it will because the first thing that we see that we must do is tend to our own heart.

10:01.986 --> 10:03.389
We must tend to our own heart.

10:03.429 --> 10:09.941
It's not something necessarily we go and do out there, but it's something that needs to be done in here.

10:09.981 --> 10:13.908
Oftentimes, we think about all that's broken in the world.

10:13.948 --> 10:23.506
We think about all that in our world that needs help and needs to be redeemed and everything in our world that needs transformation.

10:23.874 --> 10:30.502
And we look at schools and we look at politics and we look at media and we look at society and say, if only that changed.

10:30.602 --> 10:35.389
If only that was different, our kids would be okay, right?

10:35.629 --> 10:42.758
There's a lot that's broken in the world, but the word of God confronts us in a much deeper way in Deuteronomy 6.

10:43.258 --> 10:49.266
And it tells us before anything can change out there, something must change in here.

10:50.402 --> 10:53.266
that I must tend to my own heart.

10:53.306 --> 11:01.496
The starting point for passing on our faith is not the condition of the world around us, but the condition of our heart within us, right?

11:02.417 --> 11:11.007
Moses is showing us that the foundation of generational faithfulness is not instruction first, but transformation first.

11:12.589 --> 11:19.698
What isn't transformed in our lives, and I say this so many times on Wednesday night with our men, because I'm like, men,

11:19.778 --> 11:26.246
When we gather on Wednesday nights, we're seeking to be transformed because what's not transformed will be transferred.

11:27.268 --> 11:36.780
What's not transformed in our own life will leak into our families, into our marriages, into our homes, into our communities, into our workplace, in all of society.

11:37.300 --> 11:40.945
And so we must be transformed first and foremost.

11:42.487 --> 11:44.850
Moses begins with this command that is

11:44.930 --> 11:46.012
deeply personal.

11:46.192 --> 11:50.399
Love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, with all your mind.

11:50.800 --> 11:52.944
Moms and dads, adults in this room.

11:55.007 --> 11:56.910
Kids want to see.

11:56.951 --> 12:06.587
Students want to see the younger generation, the next generation to follow you wants to see is your faith real.

12:08.410 --> 12:10.674
It's not enough to just educate

12:12.258 --> 12:14.221
It's not just about education.

12:14.501 --> 12:15.963
It's about exaltation.

12:16.043 --> 12:19.028
They want to see, is your faith real?

12:20.109 --> 12:24.515
John Piper says, it's not just about education in following Jesus.

12:24.615 --> 12:27.099
It's about exaltation in following Jesus.

12:27.580 --> 12:31.966
It's not just about dry, indifferent, unemotional teaching about God.

12:32.046 --> 12:33.828
He says that's inconsistent.

12:34.209 --> 12:38.275
It says one thing about God but lives as if he's not great.

12:39.176 --> 12:40.658
We can teach all we want.

12:40.834 --> 12:47.988
But our kids are looking, they're viewing into our life and going, do they have a genuine delight about Jesus?

12:48.388 --> 12:54.079
It's not enough to show up and walk in these doors, week in and week out.

12:54.119 --> 13:04.018
They have to see it lived out in the home that your faith is genuine, that you have a love affection for Jesus above all of the things.

13:04.386 --> 13:08.072
that you treasure Jesus above all other things.

13:08.593 --> 13:13.220
This type of passion and pursuit of Jesus is contagious.

13:14.262 --> 13:23.938
In 2014, my family and I had the privilege of moving from here, Wichita Falls, Texas, to go to Salt Lake City, Utah and plant a church.

13:24.559 --> 13:26.642
And we arrive there and

13:26.786 --> 13:52.818
August of 2014 and in September of 2014, I began a residency in Little Rock, Arkansas for the next year, which meant every other week for the first year we lived in Utah, I traveled outside of the state of Utah, went to Little Rock, Arkansas, where a group of four men made an investment in me that I would still say and my wife would still say is one of the greatest gifts we've ever received as a family.

13:53.858 --> 13:57.705
In many ways, this was a finishing school for church planters.

13:58.346 --> 14:07.001
We would go, we would be invested in and they would help us and equip us to faithfully go and plant churches and cities that are in desperate need of the gospel.

14:07.882 --> 14:15.636
And so I would go and I would faithfully attend this and every other week for that year I would go and visit and these men would mentor and they would disciple us.

14:15.656 --> 14:16.818
But here's what's crazy.

14:18.178 --> 14:21.904
is there was very little equipping or teaching and preaching.

14:21.944 --> 14:24.668
There was very little teaching and equipping and counseling.

14:24.688 --> 14:30.957
There was very little teaching and equipping in terms of what it meant to be in pastoral ministry.

14:32.960 --> 14:37.367
Everything they taught us was how to follow and love Jesus.

14:39.490 --> 14:47.282
They led us to believe that if you were to have a love and pursuit of Jesus, then others would want to follow.

14:47.618 --> 15:00.951
It's the difference from standing behind a church congregation and seeking to drive them to Jesus rather than being in front of them and leading people and modeling for people what it looks like to follow Jesus.

15:01.571 --> 15:05.195
See, we need more than just educators, we need models.

15:07.136 --> 15:12.101
It's one thing to say we love Jesus, but they have to see it lived out.

15:13.162 --> 15:16.185
They need more than just instruction.

15:16.645 --> 15:17.266
So men,

15:17.666 --> 15:36.231
Fathers, leaders, moms, dads, parents, older adults in the room, her empty nesters, were called to be the visible bodily example of loving the Lord our God and loving His Word, as it says in verse six.

15:36.251 --> 15:44.882
Verse six says, and these words I command to you day, they shall be on your heart that you love God's commands, that you walk in faithfulness and obedience.

15:45.570 --> 15:47.735
Parents, can I challenge us this morning?

15:47.795 --> 15:49.238
Do your kids see you?

15:49.298 --> 15:54.569
Do they know that you wrestle and seek to walk in faithful obedience to Jesus?

15:56.714 --> 16:02.386
Do they see you come and confess areas where you're walking inconsistently with

16:02.530 --> 16:04.453
with God's word and God's commands.

16:04.513 --> 16:07.497
Do they see you be the lead repenser?

16:07.557 --> 16:18.372
I'm not calling you this morning to be a perfect father, but I am calling you to be the lead apologizer, the lead repenser, the lead confessor and point to the perfect father.

16:21.436 --> 16:29.747
As fathers, as mothers, as mentors and leaders, we are in call to embody a love for the Lord and a love for His word.

16:29.987 --> 16:31.890
The second thing He tells us is this.

16:32.450 --> 16:34.593
to teach diligently and consistently.

16:35.514 --> 16:37.256
It begins with tending our own hearts.

16:37.296 --> 16:41.101
It begins with our own love for the Lord and our own love for God's commands.

16:41.501 --> 16:45.526
But secondly, we are to teach diligently and consistently.

16:45.566 --> 16:46.387
Hear this.

16:46.487 --> 16:47.528
Hear the repetition.

16:48.810 --> 16:50.812
You shall teach them diligently to your children.

16:50.852 --> 16:53.035
You shall talk of them when you sit in your house.

16:53.155 --> 16:55.538
When you walk, by the way, when you lie down,

16:56.994 --> 17:01.980
And when you rise, you shall bind them as a sign on your hand and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.

17:02.020 --> 17:04.864
You shall write them on the doorpost of your house and on your gates.

17:05.365 --> 17:10.932
The word of God and teaching the word of God is meant to saturate your home.

17:11.592 --> 17:14.396
And here's what I would tell you this morning, okay?

17:14.416 --> 17:17.700
And Pastor Stephen, our student pastor is seated right over here.

17:17.840 --> 17:18.822
And here's what I would tell you.

17:19.723 --> 17:22.386
The home is the primary place for discipleship.

17:23.842 --> 17:38.702
If you're thinking and believing that you can drop off your student or your kid or your preschooler in one of our ministries here at church and that at 18 they will walk out mature and loving Jesus, you are greatly mistaken.

17:41.666 --> 17:47.353
Stephen would tell you he would be the first to say that this must be lived out in the home.

17:47.414 --> 17:50.738
Now I'm thankful in my own story.

17:51.618 --> 17:54.621
that there was a church like First Baptist that I could come into.

17:55.202 --> 17:59.106
When I was 18 years old, my faith preceded my parents' faith.

17:59.606 --> 18:08.755
And so as an 18-year-old, I walked into this church as a senior in high school, and I came and I sat in a room with a man named Bobby Albert, who is still a faithful member here at our church.

18:09.776 --> 18:19.506
And in that season of life, Bobby Albert had other young men that he was faithfully investing in disciple and, but he also had a home of boys of his own.

18:20.130 --> 18:23.957
But he took the responsibility of investing the next generation seriously.

18:23.977 --> 18:25.339
And I'm thankful for that.

18:25.760 --> 18:27.022
And I'm a testimony of that.

18:27.323 --> 18:45.394
And I'm thankful because I got to come and be invested in by men like Bobby Albert, by men like Jerry Royal, and people who would come and invest and shape me and transform my life so that now I can go and teach diligently to my children and in the next generation.

18:48.738 --> 18:54.554
We are called to equip the home is the primary place of discipleship.

18:54.674 --> 19:00.410
But here's what I would tell you this morning that more is caught than taught.

19:00.430 --> 19:01.673
More is caught than taught.

19:02.676 --> 19:05.042
I remember several years ago

19:05.314 --> 19:14.548
We were at home and a younger couple had called us from our church and said, hey, would you guys have time for us to come by and visit you at your house tonight?

19:14.608 --> 19:19.415
We would love to just see how your family rhythms are and like what you do as a family.

19:19.455 --> 19:20.717
And I'm all for that.

19:20.777 --> 19:22.860
I'm all about a princess-based discipleship.

19:22.920 --> 19:24.983
Come over, see what we do in our home.

19:25.264 --> 19:26.666
Now, here's what I would tell you.

19:26.866 --> 19:30.291
I was on my best behavior that night, okay?

19:30.311 --> 19:34.898
So when people come over and they're in our house, it's not that I was performing,

19:34.978 --> 19:44.754
But I did think you know what I should probably help with dishes tonight Right, I should probably get up I should go and help my wife although my wife prefers

19:44.866 --> 19:48.830
to wash dishes, she probably prefers that I help out a little more in washing dishes.

19:48.990 --> 19:53.455
And this night in particular, I was like, you know what, I'm gonna get up, I'm gonna help with dishes.

19:53.855 --> 19:58.200
And that way we can continue to engage this couple in conversation.

19:58.220 --> 20:03.485
And so I get up, I take the plates off the table, I walk over and I begin washing them.

20:03.765 --> 20:07.549
And from the dining room table, my kids in a slow clap.

20:11.613 --> 20:12.434
Dad!

20:12.962 --> 20:13.843
Good job!

20:13.983 --> 20:15.786
First time washing the dishes.

20:17.167 --> 20:19.851
And I'm thinking, man, they called me out.

20:20.151 --> 20:20.772
They called me out.

20:20.812 --> 20:22.154
They're always watching.

20:22.815 --> 20:23.395
They know.

20:23.415 --> 20:25.278
They're always seeing, right?

20:25.598 --> 20:26.880
They're always learning.

20:27.601 --> 20:28.942
But what am I reproducing?

20:29.763 --> 20:30.965
What am I reproducing?

20:31.065 --> 20:34.510
We must teach them intentionally.

20:34.990 --> 20:38.855
This word to teach them diligently is the word to impress.

20:39.256 --> 20:41.138
It means to etch in stone.

20:41.698 --> 20:45.505
I want you to think about the intentionality that we're etching in stone.

20:45.525 --> 20:52.737
When we think about our family rhythms or discipleship in our home, would we say that we're impressing these things into them?

20:52.758 --> 20:56.344
Whether we're impressing the truths of God into their life.

20:57.105 --> 21:01.533
One thing I hear far too often, okay, and I understand what you're saying.

21:02.334 --> 21:06.642
But many times I hear people say, I don't want to force my kids.

21:06.914 --> 21:09.838
I don't wanna force them to come to faith in Jesus.

21:09.878 --> 21:15.606
And here's the reality is you can't force your kids to come to Jesus, but you can create opportunities for your kids.

21:15.866 --> 21:18.330
You can impress upon them truths of Jesus.

21:19.992 --> 21:24.158
And I realize that like you're saying, I want them to own their faith.

21:24.218 --> 21:25.880
I want them to make their faith their own.

21:26.221 --> 21:35.954
I don't want that to be my doing, but can I tell you this morning that there are far too many decisions in life of lesser consequence that we force our kids to do?

21:36.738 --> 21:38.000
We force them to go to church.

21:38.040 --> 21:39.482
We force them to brush their teeth.

21:39.743 --> 21:41.085
We force them to go to bed.

21:41.145 --> 21:42.868
We force them to go to school, right?

21:43.348 --> 21:47.996
And I'm like, man, I am forcing you to come along and invest in this relationship with Jesus.

21:48.937 --> 21:50.239
And I'm commanding that.

21:50.340 --> 21:55.848
I realize that as your kids get older, you become less of a commander and more of a cult, right?

21:55.868 --> 21:58.292
And then like as they move on, you're no longer a coach.

21:58.312 --> 21:59.474
You become a consultant.

21:59.554 --> 21:59.875
Right?

22:00.295 --> 22:10.352
And they may come and approach you, but at a younger age, which is why we got to invest at a young age, we're called to command, we're called to force, we're called to impress upon them.

22:10.392 --> 22:11.374
And hear me.

22:13.097 --> 22:15.301
If you're not impressing upon them, the culture will.

22:17.064 --> 22:18.546
And they're etching it in stone.

22:19.618 --> 22:22.141
The culture is very intentional about shaping.

22:22.201 --> 22:28.429
And if your kids are not going to be impressed in your home with the truth of God's word, then social media will impress upon them.

22:28.789 --> 22:30.531
And their friends will impress upon them.

22:30.551 --> 22:32.293
And culture will impress upon them.

22:33.154 --> 22:40.143
So we must be impressing these truths, both in a systematic way and a spontaneous way.

22:40.643 --> 22:46.671
That we're to have a strong intentional discipleship plan of how we want our children to mature in faith.

22:47.191 --> 22:49.394
Now I get that that sounds intense, right?

22:49.986 --> 22:50.987
But I've seen it lived out.

22:51.669 --> 22:54.513
We spent several years, 10 years in Salt Lake City, Utah.

22:54.553 --> 23:06.451
I've seen the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints take their students and every junior high and every high school student has to go to attend seminary every morning before they go to school.

23:06.471 --> 23:08.373
They're disciplining them, I'm encouraging them.

23:08.393 --> 23:14.502
And if you know anything about these students, I mean, there's a lot that we would say is remarkable.

23:15.624 --> 23:19.570
They take discipleship, they're intense.

23:20.354 --> 23:23.160
And for Amber and I, when we were there, I go, you know what?

23:23.180 --> 23:25.666
What does it look like for us to be intentional with our kids?

23:26.367 --> 23:31.578
What does it look like for us to have a discipleship pathway where we can invest in them and strengthen them?

23:31.939 --> 23:35.146
And yes, we want it to be systematic, but also spontaneous.

23:35.286 --> 23:40.658
He says, when you sit, when you walk, when you lie down, when you rise, it's meant to be in all of life.

23:40.930 --> 23:51.781
It's not just a once a week Monday night Bible study, but it's like in all of life as you go where you go that you use every opportunity to point to Jesus in your kids' lives.

23:53.563 --> 24:00.710
Moses is assuming in this passage that there is going to be close proximity to your children.

24:02.191 --> 24:06.415
He's assuming that there is going to be close proximity.

24:06.455 --> 24:09.138
He assumes that we see

24:09.250 --> 24:11.874
and sit face to face with our children daily.

24:12.375 --> 24:15.559
Now, studies actually tell us differently.

24:15.639 --> 24:21.648
In America today, the average family in America spends 30 minutes face to face with their kids.

24:22.489 --> 24:24.412
30 minutes, okay?

24:24.432 --> 24:26.535
That's less than four to five hours per week.

24:26.595 --> 24:32.263
So if we think about, in that timeframe, can we really, are we really impressing?

24:32.303 --> 24:34.026
Are we really instilling values?

24:35.067 --> 24:37.010
Now it's gonna take much more than that.

24:37.698 --> 24:53.059
And I get that like we're already in overstressed, overworked culture, but much of what we're overstressed and overworked for is to provide more opportunities for our kids and we're missing the main thing because it's pulling us away from the investment that matters most.

24:53.840 --> 24:57.385
It's pulling us away from discipling them in the faith.

24:59.909 --> 25:03.754
So we live in a culture of scarcity, right?

25:05.897 --> 25:06.578
All of us.

25:06.914 --> 25:11.601
Never enough time, never enough accomplishment, never enough stuff, never enough impact.

25:12.141 --> 25:17.949
And maybe this week you're kind of on a never enough kind of week.

25:17.969 --> 25:23.898
I want to encourage you this morning in regards to 2 Peter chapter 1 verse 3.

25:23.978 --> 25:27.903
Here's what it says.

25:29.746 --> 25:35.634
If you feel this tension

25:36.418 --> 25:44.329
between everything that has to happen in life and the tension of going, how do I raise up the next generation?

25:44.389 --> 25:46.732
Number one, let me just say, you're already winning.

25:48.034 --> 25:52.900
If you feel that tension, if you express and experience that tension, you're already winning.

25:52.920 --> 25:56.385
The very fact that you're asking questions, how can I do a better job?

25:56.405 --> 25:57.426
You're already winning.

26:00.771 --> 26:01.952
But it's going to be difficult.

26:02.173 --> 26:03.154
It's going to be hard.

26:04.002 --> 26:14.614
And it's gonna press us into Jesus, and we're gonna have to come to a place where we are dependent upon Him to give us and sustain in us all things that pertain to life and godliness.

26:14.634 --> 26:17.977
You mean he's gonna give me everything we need for raising our kids?

26:18.017 --> 26:18.238
Yes.

26:18.618 --> 26:24.084
Do you mean he's gonna give me everything I need to be a dad, a mom, a good father, a good mother?

26:24.284 --> 26:24.845
Absolutely.

26:25.105 --> 26:30.631
Do you believe that he's gonna give you everything you need to be successful at both work and home?

26:30.651 --> 26:33.394
Yes, I believe he's going to sustain you in that.

26:33.890 --> 26:38.738
Do I believe that He's going to give you everything you need to faithfully equip the next generation?

26:39.099 --> 26:42.725
Yes, and not just in life, but for godliness.

26:42.765 --> 26:48.134
He's going to do it in a way that you can operate in a way that serves and honors God.

26:49.276 --> 26:51.039
That's amazing, right?

26:53.163 --> 26:55.026
Just let me help you understand like,

26:55.554 --> 27:00.559
The Lord's not thrown off by the fact like, oh my gosh, they have kids in work and they got a lot of things, right?

27:00.960 --> 27:04.083
No, He gave you those kids as a gift.

27:05.224 --> 27:12.652
Like He gave you those kids and He will sustain you to make the worthy investment you are to make.

27:13.853 --> 27:22.482
The third thing and last thing is this, that we are to tell the story of God's faithfulness in our home, that we're to tell the story of God's faithfulness

27:22.754 --> 27:23.215
in our home.

27:23.615 --> 27:38.373
The last few verses there, 10 through 12, we heard like, he's going to give you great and good cities that you did not build, houses full of all these good things that you did not fill, and cisterns that you did not dig, and vineyards and olive trees that you did not plant.

27:38.473 --> 27:42.198
And when you eat in full, he says, take care unless you forget the Lord.

27:42.738 --> 27:45.842
We have a habit of forgetting the Lord.

27:47.106 --> 27:53.013
We can easily look around and see all of the successes in the world and think that it's our doing.

27:54.915 --> 28:06.088
We have this home and this is my hard work and my efforts and my doing and my wit and my strength and my education that got us here.

28:07.029 --> 28:14.738
And he tells us that this is a moment of reflection when we look around and our lives are experiencing a season of blessing.

28:15.234 --> 28:23.645
that these are moments of opportunities for us to look back and point and go, let me show you how God has been faithful to us and our family.

28:25.828 --> 28:30.153
John Piper says, God does not drop a new Bible from heaven on every generation.

28:30.574 --> 28:35.360
He intends that the older generation will teach the newer generation of God's faithfulness.

28:36.341 --> 28:39.125
That's huge.

28:39.145 --> 28:43.250
So if it's easy to forget the Lord and my successes,

28:43.682 --> 28:55.800
If it's easy to forget the Lord and all the things that I feel like, and I'm failing to point to God of all the things in our life that He's been faithful in, and I haven't shepherded my family well in that.

28:56.140 --> 28:59.305
If it's easy to forget the Lord and my successes, hear me this morning.

28:59.665 --> 29:02.249
I think it's even easier to forget the Lord and my failures.

29:03.992 --> 29:05.554
And maybe that's you this morning.

29:07.170 --> 29:09.534
You're here this morning and hear me.

29:09.614 --> 29:11.196
I get that this is a heavy topic.

29:11.216 --> 29:13.139
It's a hard topic.

29:13.179 --> 29:14.741
It's challenging in many ways.

29:15.322 --> 29:21.491
And I don't know, quite honestly, that there would be any person in the room today that would be able to stand up and go, you know what?

29:22.012 --> 29:26.298
I'm nailing it at Deuteronomy chapter six.

29:26.318 --> 29:28.722
I feel like I'm knocking out the park.

29:29.090 --> 29:33.097
And today I feel good about myself because I feel like I'm crushing this.

29:33.177 --> 29:41.130
And quite honestly, I think most of us in this room are wrestling with this and trying to discover how do we faithfully do this.

29:42.733 --> 29:48.502
My hope this morning is not to make you ashamed or to discourage you, but to encourage you.

29:48.783 --> 29:55.474
My hope this morning is to help you recognize that we all fall short of this.

29:56.066 --> 30:03.614
And if I'm honest with you this morning, I fall short of this passage, dude, around me six, that I'm supposed to stand up and teach passionately.

30:03.654 --> 30:08.600
And I'm like, I think I'm passionate about it because I struggle with it the most, right?

30:09.240 --> 30:11.262
I can never perfectly model this.

30:12.224 --> 30:16.508
I can never perfectly model the love and affection we are to have towards the Lord.

30:17.269 --> 30:23.275
The love, the Lord, your God, with all in love, him above all things, with no distraction, with no thought.

30:23.316 --> 30:25.618
I'm like, man, my kids know that I love this.

30:26.754 --> 30:28.877
They see me on it, right?

30:30.520 --> 30:33.765
But do they know that I love the Lord above all others?

30:38.291 --> 30:39.173
I've been impatient.

30:40.455 --> 30:42.257
I've lacked grace in my home.

30:42.318 --> 30:43.179
I've lacked care.

30:43.239 --> 30:48.247
I've lacked fatherly affection.

30:48.267 --> 30:55.858
My job and responsibility is not to be a perfect father, but point my kids to God's faithfulness that He is

30:56.194 --> 31:03.302
the perfect Father that I come to them and I say, Jet, Lilicate, Jackson, I'm going to fail you.

31:04.644 --> 31:05.625
I have failed you.

31:06.325 --> 31:07.327
I've been impatient.

31:08.988 --> 31:10.110
I've been challenging.

31:10.550 --> 31:24.626
I've lacked grace, but there is a God who is so patient, who is so kind, who is so generous, who is so fatherly, and he's a whole lot better than me.

31:26.946 --> 31:31.052
For honest this morning, in moments of failure, we forget the Lord.

31:32.474 --> 31:36.821
In moments of failure, we forget the Lord's faithfulness.

31:38.423 --> 31:41.368
We are called and responsible to point to Him.

31:43.611 --> 31:53.746
In 2011, Shane and Shane wrote a song, and the fact that my daughter was born just a year earlier, this song really struck me.

31:55.618 --> 31:57.920
It says, I wish that I could be your everything.

31:57.960 --> 31:59.162
He's writing to his daughter.

31:59.262 --> 32:00.843
I wish I could be your everything.

32:00.964 --> 32:03.887
Be the one who gives you all the things you need.

32:03.927 --> 32:06.830
Sometimes I'm gonna let you down.

32:08.371 --> 32:13.877
But there is a way, if you just believe, he'll be your hero, like he's always been for me.

32:13.937 --> 32:17.601
Daughter, Jesus is the one you need.

32:20.384 --> 32:22.546
When I heard that song, that encourages me.

32:23.874 --> 32:29.920
Because I recognize that God the Father loves my kids way more than I could ever love them.

32:29.940 --> 32:33.764
And that God the Father is a much better shepherd than I will ever be.

32:33.804 --> 32:38.349
And my job and responsibility is to point to them.

32:38.809 --> 32:42.893
If you're here this morning, you're like, man, this is tough.

32:43.454 --> 32:45.756
Here's what I want you to be reminded of this morning.

32:46.277 --> 32:51.602
That ache you feel is not a sign of failure, but a sign of love for your kids.

32:53.378 --> 32:59.846
And you now have an opportunity to take that ache you feel and go, how can I invest?

33:00.587 --> 33:02.549
Let me give us some next steps this morning.

33:02.629 --> 33:19.329
Number one, our church, my role on staff is to help equip families, is to help reach young men and young women to faithfully disciple and raise up their families in the Lord.

33:20.251 --> 33:23.154
It would be my greatest privilege to come alongside you.

33:23.458 --> 33:26.622
Now you can imagine one guy with that responsibility that's gonna be challenging.

33:26.662 --> 33:27.283
What does that mean?

33:27.523 --> 33:28.825
That means we need mentors.

33:29.786 --> 33:32.970
We need other men and women who come alongside and invest.

33:33.510 --> 33:35.673
And that's all across the board in our church.

33:36.774 --> 33:47.608
When I think of our student ministry and our kids ministry and our preschool ministry, there are gaps and opportunities for you to step in today and come in and invest in the next generation.

33:48.349 --> 33:49.330
If you're here and you're like,

33:49.954 --> 33:50.855
How do I get involved?

33:51.055 --> 33:54.299
Come see us in the atrium, just following our worship service.

33:54.339 --> 33:57.143
We would love to talk with you and get you involved.

33:58.244 --> 34:02.029
Maybe you're here and you're a mom or dad and you're going, I want to be further shaped.

34:02.069 --> 34:03.270
I want to be equipped.

34:03.651 --> 34:04.872
We want to come alongside.

34:04.952 --> 34:06.094
We want to help you in this.

34:07.595 --> 34:09.137
Maybe you're here this morning.

34:09.177 --> 34:14.243
And you're reading this passage and you're like, you know what?

34:14.263 --> 34:19.730
How do I come to a place where I love the Lord, my God, with all my heart, my soul, my strength, my mind?

34:20.194 --> 34:22.659
Absolutely begins with a relationship with Jesus.

34:23.581 --> 34:27.628
And here in just a moment, we'd love to pray for you and encourage you to take that first step.

34:29.011 --> 34:32.297
We cannot transfer what hasn't been transformed in us.

34:32.358 --> 34:34.462
So this morning, maybe you need to come.

34:35.604 --> 34:37.848
Maybe this morning you need to come and pray for your family.

34:37.888 --> 34:42.898
Maybe this morning you need to come and pray with your wife and ask the Lord, Lord, help us.

34:43.458 --> 34:45.080
Give us strength sustain us.

34:45.441 --> 34:48.665
Your word tells us you've given us everything we need for life and God in this.

34:48.765 --> 34:51.990
Help us be faithful to this calling in Deuteronomy 6.

34:52.531 --> 34:53.692
What are you investing in?

34:54.473 --> 34:59.821
Are you investing where it matters most?

34:59.841 --> 35:03.085
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

35:03.666 --> 35:12.338
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

35:12.578 --> 35:13.906
We'll see you next week.

